Attention is the core mechanism that allows chat AI systems to understand which words in your message are most relevant to each other. When you type a sentence like "The chef prepared the meal that the critic loved," attention helps the AI figure out that "loved" connects to "critic" (who did the loving) and "meal" (what was loved), even though other words sit between them. This ability to dynamically focus on relevant parts of the input is what enables these systems to maintain coherent context across long conversations and understand complex, multi-part questions where different pieces of information need to connect to form meaning.
